did.head: Overview of the Collection
did.abstract: This is a collection of primarily photographs and negatives that appeared in the Ohio State University College of Medicine Journal.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content
scopecontent.p: The Jane Sedgwick Papers (approximately 10.5 linear feet) is a compilation of material that documents the Ohio State University College of Medicine Journal during Sedgwickâ€™s time as Managing Editor. The collection is comprised mainly of photographs.

arrangement.head: Statement of Arrangement
arrangement.p: Series I: Departments (2 box) documents various medical center departments and groups. The series is arranged alphabetically. Series II: Events (2 boxes) documents various events held by the medical center. The series is arranged alphabetically. Series III: Other (2 boxes) is comprised of material of a more general nature. The series is arranged alphabetically. Series IV: People (5 boxes) documents people who work or worked in the medical center. The series is arranged alphabetically by a person's last name.

accessrestrict.head: Restrictions on Access
accessrestrict.p:
The collection is open to the public and is available for viewing in the Medical Heritage Center. Materials do not circulate and must be used in the supervised reading room.
Restrictions, including copyright, may exist and some materials may be too fragile to photocopy or digitize. The MHC charges for duplication services, which must be performed by staff.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: [Identification of item], Jane Sedgwick Papers, Spec.199817.Sedgwick, Medical Heritage Center, Health Sciences Library, The Ohio State University.
